First install node.js, like so (on Ubuntu):

    sudo apt-get install python-software-properties
    sudo add-apt-repository ppa:chris-lea/node.js
    sudo apt-get update
    sudo apt-get install nodejs

Then install jade. Easiest way to do that is if you first install npm, like so:

    sudo apt-get install npm

and then:

    npm install jade

Configure the selenium servers (nodes) in the servers.js
Start the hub with "nodejs app.js"